TITLE: "This Halloween, What Are New Jersey Voters Really Afraid Of? More Than Half Say the 2024 Election."
AUTHOR: Rutgers University-New Brunswick
DESCRIPTION: When asked how the upcoming 2024 presidential election makes them feel, a majority of New Jersey voters express some kind of dread, according to the latest Rutgers-Eagleton Poll. Fifty-seven percent say something about being anxious (15%), nervous (14%), uneasy (12%), scared (12%) or worried (4%). Eight percent cite being excited, optimistic or hopeful.
